description.narrative:
The objectives of the intervention are:

- evaluate the degradation trends in each geographical region of the country;

- determine the degradation hotspots for each region and propose neutrality indicators as well as measures to attain these;

- validate the generated information for each region and prepare an action plan for each region as well as for the whole country;

- integrate the generated information into national and regional policies and programs, including the Programme National du Secteur Rural (PNSR3);

- identify transformative projects/programs and innovative financing mechanisms for achieving soil neutrality in Burkina Faso.
